50|$|Saurida undosquamis {{also known}} as the Brushtooth {{lizardfish}} or Large-scale grinner is a type of lizardfish, a <b>demersal</b> <b>species</b> that occurs in the Eastern Indian Ocean, Malay Peninsula, northern Java, Arafura Sea, Louisiade Archipelago, southern Philippines and northern Australia,. Reports of its occurrence in the Red Sea region and introduction to the Mediterranean are questionable,.|$|R
50|$|The {{speckled}} catshark {{is known}} from the Gulf of Aden, and {{off the coast of}} Somalia, with a separate population extending from Viet Nam and the Philippines, through Indonesia to Western Australia. It is a <b>demersal</b> <b>species,</b> living on continental shelves and insular shelves, with a depth range of between 37 and 250 m.|$|R
